<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Andros Townsend revealed that he was confident that Crystal Palace could catch Manchester United cold at Old Trafford.</p>

<p>United had a delayed start to the new campaign following their involvement in Europe at the end of last season and they were far from at their best on Saturday, with Palace securing a 3-1 victory.</p>

<p>Townsend found the net in the seventh minute to put Palace ahead, with Wilfried Zaha scoring a brace, which ensured a frustrating time for United, despite debutant Donny van de Beek's goal. </p>

<p>Andros Townsend revealed he was confident Crystal Palace could beat Manchester United</p>

<p>It has been a superb start to the Premier League campaign for Palace, with this victory following on from their success against Southampton last weekend. </p>

<p>Asked whether he is surprised by Palace's start to the season, Townsend told Sky Sports: 'No we know we have a good enough squad. We added one or two young players and are fully confident. </p>

<p>Townsend played a significant part as Palace continued their encouraging start to the season</p>

<p>'With United having their first game here we thought we could catch them cold. Once we get ahead we're a well drilled team and knew we had enough to stay in front. Mentally we knew we had an advantage. </p>

<p>'We knew if we started fast we might catch them cold and then it was a point of seeing out the game plan.'</p>

<p>It was a particularly special occasion for Zaha, who endured a hugely frustrating spell at United between 2013 and 2015.</p>

<p>Townsend was full of praise for team-mate Wilfried Zaha, describing his display as 'incredible'</p>

<p>Townsend was full of praise for what he described as an 'incredible' performance from Zaha. </p>

<p>Townsend said: 'Wilf Zaha was incredible. He's shown that in the last six or seven years. It was a real captain's performance and hope he can carry that on for a while yet.'</p>

<p>Next up for Palace is a home game against Everton, who have also started the season very well.  </p>
